{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented in [`flow_autotts/controllers/optimal.py`](/inspire/hdd/global_user/gongjingjing-25039/sywang/jkcai/FlowEvo/flow_autotts/controllers/optimal.py).\n\n**Controller**\nA beta-smooth scout/confirm/prune/refine policy: low beta stays near deterministic ODE anchoring, mid beta adds preview-guided width plus selective backward children, high beta keeps more contenders alive and branches from the best confirmed anchors.\n\n**Inspected**\nI read [`flow_tts_controller_implementation_spec.md`](/inspire/hdd/global_user/gongjingjing-25039/sywang/jkcai/FlowEvo/flow_tts_controller_implementation_spec.md), the context pack at [`context_pack.md`](/inspire/hdd/global_user/gongjingjing-25039/sywang/jkcai/FlowEvo/logs/flow_autotts/pickscore_sd35/train_codex_bestof4_ode_clean_b128/codex_logs/r0000_20260521_092626_8464683a/context_pack.md), [`flow_autotts/controllers/optimal.py`](/inspire/hdd/global_user/gongjingjing-25039/sywang/jkcai/FlowEvo/flow_autotts/controllers/optimal.py), and [`flow_autotts/controllers/baselines.py`](/inspire/hdd/global_user/gongjingjing-25039/sywang/jkcai/FlowEvo/flow_autotts/controllers/baselines.py). The `history/` directory had no prior round files, and the snapshot directory only contained the rendered prompt/context pack, so there were no earlier controller snapshots to diff against.\n\nThe only frontier rows available were the ODE baseline rows:\n- beta `0.0`: reward `0.6765`, mean NFE `8`\n- beta `0.25`: reward `0.8167`, mean NFE `24`\n- beta `0.5`: reward `0.8422`, mean NFE `44`\n- beta `0.75`: reward `0.8481`, mean NFE `72`\n- beta `1.0`: reward `0.8495`, mean NFE `100`\n\n**Schedule**\n- `beta<=0`: deterministic anchor, `latest_active`\n- `scouts = 1 + [β>0] + [β>=0.33] + [β>=0.66] + [β>=0.9]`\n- `first_probe_time = grid(round((0.18 + 0.10β) * last_idx))`\n- `second_probe_time = grid(round((0.50 + 0.18β) * last_idx))`\n- `child_time = grid(round((0.82 - 0.22β) * last_idx))`\n- `keep_base = 1 + [β>=0.40] + [β>=0.80]`\n- `finish_base = 1 + [β>=0.45] + [β>=0.85]`\n- `branch_base = [β>=0.35] + [β>=0.75] + [β>=0.95]`\n- `noise_policy = inferred_noise` if `β<0.55`, else `mixed_noise`\n- `noise_strength = clamp(0.84 - 0.44β, 0.25, 0.85)`\n\nBudget use is monotonic because higher beta increases scout count, keep/finish/branch counts, and shifts refinement earlier enough to make backward/finish chains more expensive.\n\n**What’s new**\nThis is behaviorally different from the previous best-of-N style controller: it uses preview gaps and uncertainty to decide keep/prune/branch, adds a second confirmation probe, and allocates backward children selectively from ranked anchors instead of finishing every root then refining uniformly.\n\n**Checks**\n- `python3 -m py_compile flow_autotts/controllers/optimal.py`\n- `python3` fake-env dry run across beta `0.0/0.25/0.5/0.75/1.0` to exercise `spawn/forward/preview/backward/prune/answer`\n\n**Risks**\nPreview score calibration may still dominate branch selection; the main expected gains are at beta `0.25`, `0.5`, and `0.75`. Beta `0.0` underuse is justified. Beta `0.25` is intentionally conservative to avoid losing to ODE. Beta `0.5+` was adjusted upward to use more of the target compute."}}
